  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Customer Service Associate (Retail)",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Description:</strong></u></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Operations</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Responsible for the daily operations of retail outlet</li>\n  <li>Monitor sales &amp; manage inventory level to ensure adequate stock to maximize sales</li>\n  <li>Responsible for the stock variance within his/her shop</li>\n  <li>Assist in manpower planning</li>\n  <li>Maintain high level of customer service standards</li>\n  <li>Create a friendly and yet competitive sales environment to maximize sales output</li>\n  <li>Ensure in-store display is carried out according to VM instruction or guideline</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Staff Management</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Coach and supervise staff in correct execution of all company operations</li>\n  <li>Coach and counsel staff with regard to the standard set by the company</li>\n  <li>Ensure that staff adheres to company's code of conduct &amp; ensure fair practice at work</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>GCE \"O\", \"N\" Level or ITE certificate</li>\n  <li>2 to 3 years of sales experience or customer service experience</li>\n  <li>Willing to work on weekends and public holidays (6 days workweek)</li>\n  <li>Excellent verbal communication and selling-up skills</li>\n  <li>Strong orientation towards providing excellent customer service</li>\n  <li>Team player</li>\n</ul>",
